<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>William Held</title>
  <link rel="icon" href="images/favicon.png">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Raleway:400,300,600" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/skeleton/2.0.4/skeleton.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">
  <style>
    body { font-family: 'Raleway', sans-serif; color: #222; }
    h4 { letter-spacing: .1rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .header { margin-top: 60px; margin-bottom: 60px; }
    .paper { margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.2; }
    .paper p { margin-bottom: 2px; }
    .paper-buttons { margin-top: 2px; }
    .paper .button { display: inline-block; height: 20px; padding: 0 5px; font-weight: 100; line-height: 20px; margin-bottom: 0; text-transform: none; }
    .docs-section { border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding: 4rem 0; }
    .scroll-container { overflow-x: auto; white-space: nowrap; padding-bottom: 10px; }
    .scroll-container .paper { display: inline-block; margin-right: 10px; vertical-align: top; }
    footer { text-align: center; color: rgba(0,0,0,0.4); border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding: 15px 0 40px; }
    .profile-pic {
      border-radius: 50%;
      width: 150px;
      height: 150px;
      object-fit: cover;
    }
    .main-description h2,
    .main-description h3,
    .main-description h4,
    .main-description p {
      font-size: 0.5em;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <section class="header">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="three columns">
          <img class="u-max-full-width profile-pic" src="images/profile.jpeg" alt="Profile">
        </div>
        <div class="nine columns main-description">
          <h1>William Held</h1>
          <h3>PhD Student at Georgia Tech, Visiting Researcher at Stanford</h3>
          <h4>held@stanford.edu</h4>
          <h2>Bio</h2>
          <p>I am currently a PhD student in Machine Learning at Georgia Tech, advised by Prof. <a href="https://cs.stanford.edu/~diyiy/">Diyi Yang</a>, and a visiting researcher at the Stanford NLP Group.</p>
          <p>My research develops methods to improve the robustness and fairness of language technology across domains and modalities. The goal of my research is to language technology more flexible to adaptation in order to broaden the number of people who can leverage it for innovation. During my PhD, I have worked on </p>
          <h3>Language, Dialect, and Domain Robustness</h3>
          <p>Ensuring language technology can be quickly adapted to perform reliably across diverse settings with little to no additional data.</p>
          <h3>Social Factors in NLP</h3>
          <p>Understanding how human social systems inform and affect the performance of language technology for different user groups.</p>
          <h3>Speech Processing &amp; Voice Assistant</h3>
          <p>Extending language technology to more speech in order to provide help to users more naturally and efficiently.</p>
          <p>Previously, I was an early engineer at <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2020/11/18/marissa-mayers-startup-launches-its-first-official-product-sunshine-contacts/">Sunshine AI</a>, where I worked on AI to "<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o5X-7x0iq_g">make the mundane magical</a>" under <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/marissamayer/">Marissa Mayer</a>. I earned my undergraduate degree from NYU Abu Dhabi, working on lexical semantics and Arabic NLP advised by Prof. <a href="https://nyuad.nyu.edu/en/academics/divisions/science/faculty/nizar-habash.html">Nizar Habash</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="six columns">
        <h5>General Links</h5>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="me" href="https://www.threads.net/@william.held">Bluesky</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://twitter.com/WilliamBarrHeld">Twitter</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/williambarrheld/">LinkedIn</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/Helw150">Github</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="six columns">
        <h5>Academic Links</h5>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="files/res.pdf">Resume</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/William-B.-Held/46552910">Semantic Scholar</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=SP9VJNkAAAAJ&amp;hl=en">Google Scholar</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://dblp.org/pid/245/8601.html">DBLP</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {% if notebooks or apps %}
  <div class="container docs-section">
    <div class="row">
      {% if notebooks %}
      <div class="six columns">
        <h4>Notebooks</h4>
        <div class="scroll-container">
          {% for notebook in notebooks %}
          <!-- {{ notebook.display_name }} Notebook -->
          <div class="paper">
            <p class="title">{{ notebook.display_name }}</p>
            <div class="paper-buttons">
              <a href="{{ notebook.html_path }}" class="button">Open Notebook</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endif %}

      {% if apps %}
      <div class="six columns">
        <h4>Apps</h4>
        <div class="scroll-container">
          {% for app in apps %}
          <!-- {{ app.display_name }} App -->
          <div class="paper">
            <p class="title">{{ app.display_name }}</p>
            <div class="paper-buttons">
              <a href="{{ app.html_path }}" class="button">Open App</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

